The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Dravid lone player to meet BCCI

Mumbai: No Indian player other than captain Rahul Dravid will be called when the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) officials meet here on April 6 to review the teams World Cup debacle. 

No player other than Dravid, who is to be present at the morning review meeting with the BCCI office bearers, will be called on April 6, said a BCCI source Wednesday. 

Also present at the meeting would be selection committee chairman Dilip Vengsarkar, coach Greg Chappell and manager Sanjay Jagdale, who is also a member of the five-member selection committee. 

On Tuesday, joint secretary M. P. Pandove had said that senior players could be asked to attend the meeting if deemed necessary. 

The BCCI office-bearers meeting with seven ex-captains is scheduled for Friday afternoon. (PTI) 




